casebody.data:
No. 128,

Misc.

Bell v. Texas. Petitioner pro se. Wag-goner Can, Attorney General of Texas, Hawthorne Phillips, First Assistant Attorney General, T. B. Wright, Executive Assistant Attorney General, and Howard M. Fender, Gilbert J. Pena and Charles B. Swanner, Assistant Attorneys General, for respondent.

Ct. Crim. App. Tex. Motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and petition for writ of certiorari granted. The case is transferred to the appellate docket.
